 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uharryh0od.showPublicProfile?language=EN>harryh0od</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/12/01 5:58:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=322.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Top Ten Poisons-PVP emphasis</span><hr size=1> I don't play on a PvP server but I do duel a lot in the Arena...<br>
<br>
 One of my favorite poisons is System Shock.  It's a nice DD with a stun and push back.  Run up, stun (interrupt casting if a caster <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START >: --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/mad.gif ALT=">:"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )  and circle 'round him for a goos ol' Backstab.  <br>
<br>
  I've killed many casters with this <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
 -Hood <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umordier.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mordier</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/12/01 8:44:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=322.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Top Ten Poisons-PVP emphasis</span><hr size=1> It really depends on your opponent and your surroundings.<br>
<br>
Root poisons are great in most cases, and easy to make/raise skill because you can buy the components.  Use root against casters (can mean a quick death) and some hybrids.  It has limited use against melees, as you usually don't want to go toe to toe with a weighted axe-weilding warrior.<br>
<br>
Snare poisons are my favorite.  They work well for casters AND melee and tend to last a long time.  They also tend to give the victim a false sense of escape (unlike root) which will often lead to silly mistakes.<br>
<br>
Blind poisons work great as well, but you have to be in the right area to use them.  If they have sow, and you don't, a blind opponent in the Karanas can just run away without fear of mobs (or you).<br>
<br>
Against melees I usually go for damage (or snare).  The system shock series is very nice.<br>
<br>
Morvran McGuinness, Shanks   VZ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=nocha>Nocha</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/12/01 10:19:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=322.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Top Ten Poisons-PVP emphasis</span><hr size=1> cool, i apreciate the tutilage, <br>
