</table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=cylant>Cylant</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/13/01 6:20:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=322.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Top Ten Poisons-PVP emphasis</span><hr size=1> Tiig told me something about using weaken poisons against casters, for the snare effect, and i think it might be a pretty good idea, seeing how weaken lasts a long time.<br>
I personally carry around spike break, muscle lock, and retinal deactivator I.  Usually around 10 at a time, that'll last me about a week. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umordier.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mordier</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/13/01 9:31:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=322.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Top Ten Poisons-PVP emphasis</span><hr size=1> Ah, the weaken poison!  I completely forgot about this group of poisons.  He's right, against the right opponent this can be as good as a snare, and much easier to get components.<br>
<br>
For intelligence casters it usually works like a charm.  But it also works great (and often best) on smaller race/melee combinations.  Dark elves of any class (especially warriors/SKs), gnomes, clerics, etc...   <br>
<br>
It can also work in the right situation.  For instance, chances are good in a dungeon that your opponent has been hanging out there for a long time and made some good plat (and gold and silver and copper) along with other loot like fine steel weapons.  They're probably close to being encumbered regardless of race.<br>
<br>
In short, weaken poisons are the poor man's snare, but when used right they'll get you the same result AND are easier to make.  Just save those spider sacks.<br>
<br>
Morvran McGuinness <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucoyoteblack.showPublicProfile?language=EN>coyoteblack</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/13/01 10:04:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=322.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Top Ten Poisons-PVP emphasis</span><hr size=1> Against monks weaken is the best. I like blind/root against casters depending if I really want there gear or just ensure that they die. <br>
<br>
I think the hardest part is collecting regents and making sure you always increase skill. For some reason my level 1 poisons get resisted way more then levels 2 even on the same opponent<br>
<br>
I also like to hotkey a poison after applying one to my blade. If you do this you can get a root/blind or blind/weaken off kind of fast.<br>
 <p>" No matter how subtle the wizard, a knife between the shoulder blades will seriously cramp his style"  -- Vlad Taltos</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uceescritdabossalini.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ceescrit da Bossalini</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/13/01 10:22:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=322.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Top Ten Poisons-PVP emphasis</span><hr size=1> In my experience, here's my list of favorite poisons for just taking somone out (and I've used tons of them).<br>
<br>
1. Muscle Lock (snare)- Great in just about all situations, if it sticks and lasts, that is.  Seems to last longer than the Paralyze series.<br>
<br>
2.  Paralyze (root + slow)- This is great too, when it sticks and lasts for full duration.  Especially great for going toe to toe with another duel wielding opponent, because of the slow effect it provides.  Its also really easy to land backstabs on a rooted PC.<br>
<br>
3.  Blind- This can be great in certain situations.  I've also never had issues with it wearing off too fast either.  In enclosed spaces, or against somone that is unsowed (and you being sowed or Jboots) this can be very good to use.  Out in the open, this poison is about worthless though against somone with half a brain.  All they have to do is run around in circles and use ghosting/lag to avoid being meleed.  Teamed with another rogue using root or snare, this is the ultimate combo.<br>
<br>
4.  System Shock- Does a bit more damage than contact I think, and the stun is also nice for landing an initial backstab.<br>
<br>
5.  Beserker Madness- The must underrated poison that exists, in my opinion.  Does more overall damage than any poison there is.  Just don't use this one and try to tank another melee, you'll get hurt.  If that's the case, hit them with it, then bow kite them around untill it wears off.<br>
<br>
6.  Contact and injected- both are good and cheap poisons to use.  You always get the full effect, if they aren't resisted initially.  Injected does more overall damage.<br>
<br>
7. Lower resists- Can be nice when teamed with another caster for taking people out quick. <p><font size=4 face=Times New Roman, serif><b>Ceescrit Bossalini</font><BR>
